replies.author: @sheepdipped
replies.text: If you haven't seen it yet, there's a documentary by the Irish Film Board from 2002/2003 where they were doing a piece on Chavez, but they ended up capturing a coup in real time. The US-backed 'opposition' kidnapped president Chavez. It's called 'The Revolution will not be Televised.' It was extremely eye-opening for me when I first watched it. Unlike many related historical events, it had more of a happy ending too. It really speaks volumes for the people of Venezuela. They were the real heroes in the end.
